  <abstract displayLabel="Description">Rivers discusses her father's service in World War II, business, and civil rights efforts in Baton Rouge; her role in the integration of Robert E. Lee High School; her role in the LSU desegregation suit; and her attendance at LSU, including her racist reception by other students.  Rivers also discusses her participation in the civil rights movement, her work with inner-city children, African-American politics and voting, the challenges facing African Americans, and the future of race relations in America.</abstract>
